    <strong>?? Important Security Rules:</strong>
    <ul>
        <li>Never share your private keys or seed phrase with anyone Ã�š”” not even "support" staff</li>
        <li>Write your 12-24 word seed phrase on paper and store it in a safe place (not a screenshot, not in cloud storage)</li>
        <li>Always send a small test transaction before moving your full balance</li>
        <li>Double-check wallet addresses Ã�š”” copy-paste, never type manually</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<h2>The Dogecoin Tipping Culture</h2>

<p>Dogecoin's tipping culture is one of the most unique features of the community. The idea is simple: if someone creates valuable content, helps you, or makes you laugh, you tip them a few Dogecoins. Because DOGE transactions cost less than a penny and confirm in one minute, it's practical to tip small amounts.</p>

<p><strong>Origins of tipping:</strong> In 2014, Reddit's Dogetipbot allowed users to tip DOGE via Reddit comments with commands like "+/u/dogetipbot 100 doge". At its peak, the bot processed thousands of tips daily. Though Dogetipbot shut down in 2017, the tipping culture lives on through:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Twitter/X tipping:</strong> Elon Musk enabled DOGE tipping on X (formerly Twitter) via the Tips feature</li>
    <li><strong>MyDoge Wallet:</strong> A mobile-first wallet with built-in tipping functionality</li>
    <li><strong>Community Discord/Telegram bots:</strong> Many Dogecoin community servers have tip bots for small transactions</li>
</ul>

<p>The tipping spirit goes beyond individual tips Ã�š”” the Dogecoin community has a long history of charitable giving through micro-donations:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>2014: Jamaican Bobsled Team</strong> Ã�š”” Raised ~$30,000 worth of DOGE to send the team to the Sochi Winter Olympics</li>
    <li><strong>2014: Clean Water in Kenya</strong> Ã�š”” Donated ~$11,000 to build a well in Kenya (sponsored by Doge4Water)</li>
    <li><strong>2014: NASCAR Sponsorship</strong> Ã�š”” Crowdfunded ~$55,000 in DOGE to sponsor NASCAR driver Josh Wise (the car featured the Doge meme)</li>
    <li><strong>2021: DOGE-1 Moon Mission</strong> Ã�š”” Funded a SpaceX lunar payload entirely in Dogecoin</li>
</ul>

<h2>Merchant Adoption Ã�š”” Where Can You Spend Dogecoin?</h2>

<p>Dogecoin is accepted by hundreds of merchants worldwide. Here are some notable examples:</p>

<table>
    <tr>
        <th>Merchant</th>
        <th>What You Can Buy</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>Dallas Mavericks</strong></td>
        <td>Tickets, merchandise (processed 20,000+ DOGE transactions in 2021)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>Newegg</strong></td>
        <td>Electronics, computer parts (via BitPay DOGE support)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>BitPay Merchants</strong></td>
        <td>Thousands of merchants using BitPay can accept DOGE Ã�š”” including AMC Theatres, AirBaltic, and more</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>NOWPayments Merchants</strong></td>
        <td>100+ online stores via NOWPayments DOGE integration</td>
    </tr>
